  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "9585653e-0c73-4db3-bbde-d5cf7733f9fa",
      "type": "core",
      "title": "ThonkBoard",
      "body": "- AI-powered mind map builder designed to help you think.\n- Start by creating a core node for your idea, project, or topic, then branch out with questions, ideas, and problems.\n- Build paths on an infinite canvas, easily moving and reattaching nodes as your thoughts evolve.\n- Master the interface with deep keyboard-first navigation, using a spatial algorithm that selects the node with the closest centroid projection along the selected axis of movement.\n- Keep keyboard controls as an opt-in power user feature to ensure the experience remains intuitive for casual users.\n- Use AI to challenge your ideas or suggest new directions; the system maintains coherence in large projects by feeding the model relevant local neighborhoods of your graph rather than linear tokens.\n- Resolve nodes once you've finished a thought; it's a \"fire and forget\" way to clear clutter while the board keeps the project context for you.\n- Export your entire thought process to JSON or markdown to save your progress elsewhere or share your maps.\n- It is free to use, though there is a button in the top corner if you feel like buying me a coffee.\n- Everything stays private because there is no backend; all data is stored locally in your browser's localStorage.\n- While local storage keeps things simple and avoids backend costs, you can manually save your work to your own drive to prevent data loss.\n- While primarily browser-based, you can run it offline using local tools like Ollama, provided your hardware has enough power to support the AI models.",
      "summary": "",
      "resolved": false,
      "conflicts": [],
      "position": {
        "x": 702.6035583611176,
        "y": 133.34222167403175
      },
      "meta": {
